docs {
  # LuminaVaultServer

  Bruno collection for LuminaVault HTTP API.

  ## Environments
  - **local** — docker-compose dev, `http://localhost:8080`
  - **dev** — staging, fill `baseUrl` in `environments/dev.bru`
  - **prod** — production, fill `baseUrl` in `environments/prod.bru`

  ## Folders
  - **Auth/** — register, login (with optional MFA), refresh, logout, MFA verify/resend, OAuth exchange, forgot/resend/reset password, GET `/me`
  - **WebAuthn/** — passkey registration + authentication (4 endpoints).
    Requires `webauthn.enabled=true` and a real authenticator (Bruno cannot
    mint `attestationObject`/`authenticatorData` blobs — drive from the iOS
    client via `ASAuthorizationPlatformPublicKeyCredentialProvider` or a
    browser test page). `Authenticate Finish` returns full JWT tokens.
  - **Devices/** — register/unregister APNS device tokens for the
    authenticated user. Required before `LLM/Chat` produces a push.
  - **LLM/** — `POST /v1/llm/chat` proxies to the user's Hermes profile
    via `http://hermes:8642/v1/chat/completions`. Profile name == username.
  - **Memory/** — `POST /v1/memory/upsert` and `POST /v1/memory/search`
    (Hermes tool-calling for writes + reads), plus `POST /v1/query`
    (chat-style natural-language search) and `POST /v1/memos` (Hermes
    writes a synthesizing markdown memo + saves it to the vault under
    `memos/<date>/<slug>.md` with `[[memory:<uuid>]]` citations).
  - **Vault/** — `POST /v1/vault/files?path=...` writes raw bytes
    (markdown / image) into the user's `tenants/<userID>/raw/<path>`
    directory. Server sanitizes the path, whitelists Content-Type, caps
    body at 10 MB, and writes atomically. Hermes sees the file via the
    shared `./data` mount.
  - **KB/** — `POST /v1/kb-compile` ingests a JSON batch of files (text
    + base64), writes each into the raw vault, then drives the Hermes
    profile through a learning loop with `memory_upsert` exposed.
    Returns written files, distilled memories, and a synthesized
    summary in one shot.
  - **Spaces/** — CRUD for user-defined organizing folders (e.g. AI,
    Stocks, Health). `GET/POST /v1/spaces`, `GET/PUT/DELETE
    /v1/spaces/:id`. Creating a space creates an on-disk folder under
    `tenants/<userID>/raw/<slug>/`; subsequent vault uploads with
    `path=<slug>/<filename>.md` land inside the space. Slug is locked
    at create; display name is mutable.
  - **Health/** — `POST /v1/health` ingests a JSON batch of HealthKit /
    Google Fit / manual events into `health_events` (tenant-scoped
    time-series). Generic schema covers sleep, HRV, resting HR,
    recovery scores, steps, weight, mindful minutes — anything with a
    `(type, recordedAt, value)` shape. Batch capped at 1000.
  - **Admin/** — Hermes profile reconciliation. `GET .../health` (count
    snapshot), `POST .../reconcile` (idempotent ensure-loop over every
    user), `POST .../reap-orphans` (soft-delete fs dirs without DB row).
    Gated by `X-Admin-Token` matching `admin.token` server config; 404
    when token unset. **Not** JWT-protected — separate operator path.

  ## Token flow
  Register / Login / Refresh / OAuth Exchange / WebAuthn Finish all auto-store
  `accessToken`, `refreshToken`, `userId`, `mfaChallengeId`, `webauthnCredentialID`
  into the active environment via post-response scripts. Protected requests
  read those vars automatically.

  Standard run: `Auth/Register` → `Auth/Me` → `LLM/Chat`. Optional follow-ups:
  `Devices/Register Device` to wire APNS, `WebAuthn/*` after passkey enrolment.

  ## WebSocket testing — `/v1/ws`
  Bruno does not speak `ws://`. Use `websocat` or `wscat`:

  ```
  brew install websocat        # macOS
  npm i -g wscat               # alternative

  # Get an accessToken from Auth/Login first, then:
  websocat -H="Authorization: Bearer <accessToken>" ws://localhost:8080/v1/ws

  # Type any text -> the server broadcasts it back to every active
  # connection of the same tenant (ConnectionManager). Use a second
  # terminal to confirm same-tenant fan-out.
  ```

  Disconnect by Ctrl-C. Server logs `websocket connected` /
  `websocket disconnected` with `tenant_id` and `username` metadata.
}
